{
  "name": "Slow Reflexes",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Whenever the sage deals damage to an opponent using his chi gong ability, he may spend a ki point to twine his ki throughout his opponent&#8217;s body, hindering their movement and slowing their reactions. The opponent must succeed at a Fortitude save or take a penalty to their Reflex saving throws and attack rolls made as part of an attack of opportunity equal to the number of chi gong dice the sage possesses (so a 5th level sage would inflict a -3 penalty) until the end of the sage&#8217;s next turn; multiple uses of this ability do not stack.</p>\n",
